  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I want to have the send button of a spamming user's app be disabled for a certain period after each sent message so that spamming a chat is less feasible for him.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Feature or Bug? i.e Type: Bug)\r\n*Type*: Feature\r\n\r\n[comment]: # (Describe the feature you would like, or briefly summarise the bug and what you did, what you expected to happen, and what actually happens. Sections below)\r\n*Summary*: Currently, it is very easy for a user to spam a public chat by pasting some long message over and over again. If we disable the send button for an increasing amount of time each time that a user sends messages in quick succession, we can discourage that behavior.\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what you expected to happen.)\r\n- User sends message 1\r\n- User sends message 2 within 1 second\r\n- App notices that the user is sending messages in quick succession and increases the timeout during which the Send button is disabled to 2 seconds.\r\n- User sends another message right after the button is enabled again.\r\n- App increases timeout to 5 seconds.\r\n\r\nNote: There is a cooldown period of 10 seconds, after which we reset the timeout. These values should be easy to change so we can experiment with them.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n[comment]: # (Describe what actually happened.)\r\n- User is able to send messages in quick succession without any limits.\r\n",
